OL,3,C2024 set to be hottest year on record,
OL,4,Ccapping a 'decade of deadly heat'
OL,6,FThe UN's climate and weather agency,
OL,7,Fthe World Meteorological Organisation
OL,8,F(WMO), will publish official
OL,9,Ftemperature figures for the year in
OL,10,FJanuary.
OL,12,FRecord-breaking temperatures in 2024
OL,13,Ffollow a decade of unprecedented heat
OL,14,Ffuelled by human activities, and
OL,15,Fdriving increasing weather extremes.
OL,17,FGreenhouse gas levels continue to
OL,18,Freach new highs, locking in more heat
OL,19,Ffor the future, the agency warned.
