OL,3,C2024 set to be hottest year on record,
OL,4,Ccapping a 'decade of deadly heat'
OL,6,F"In 2025, countries must put the world
OL,7,Fon a safer path by dramatically
OL,8,Fslashing emissions and supporting the
OL,9,Ftransition to a renewable future. It
OL,10,Fis essential, and it is possible."
OL,12,FWMO secretary-general Celeste Saulo
OL,13,Fsaid every degree of warming matters
OL,14,Fand leads to increased climate
OL,15,Fextremes, with temperatures "only part
OL,16,Fof the picture".
